│ 3818 /// VPRegionBlock represents a collection of VPBasicBlocks and         │
│ VPRegionBlocks                                                              │
│ 3819 /// which form a Single-Entry-Single-Exiting subgraph of the output IR │
│ CFG.                                                                        │
│ 3820 /// A VPRegionBlock may indicate that its contents are to be           │
│ replicated several                                                          │
│ 3821 /// times. This is designed to support predicated scalarization, in    │
│ which a                                                                     │
│ 3822 /// scalar if-then code structure needs to be generated VF * UF times. │
│ Having                                                                      │
│ 3823 /// this replication indicator helps to keep a single model for        │
│ multiple                                                                    │
│ 3824 /// candidate VF's. The actual replication takes place only once the   │
